==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Communicant
<hw>Com*mu"ni*cant</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧m*m⟦umac⟧"n⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧nt)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>communicans</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who partakes of, or is entitled to partake of, the sacrament of
the Lord's supper; a church member.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A never-failing monthly <qex>communicant</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who communicates.</def>
<rj><au>Foxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Communicant</ent>⟦br⟧

